              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>So rag/adaptive.py is the largest file in the codebase and the most sophisticated. It's the adapter layer between the RAG engine contract and PostgreSQL. EvidenceLedger deduplicates and grades — every chunk enters with its strategy tag. If the same chunk appears in vector and keyword results, it scores higher but only counts once. apply_grades() attaches LLM judge scores 0-1. materialize_documents() selects the best max_chunks using vector similarity, keyword score, and judge grade. CorpusRetrievalAdapter.search_corpus() runs hybrid retrieval with vector and keyword, then merges and deduplicates. _rerank_with_query_heuristics() gives a bonus to docs whose titles match query terms. _rewrite_query() calls the judge to rephrase ambiguous queries. The multi-round loop is adaptive: it monitors coverage after each round and decides whether another round with different strategies is needed.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
